# Slidr — Dual License

Copyright © 2026 Tushar Aggarwal · [Uitbreiden](https://uitbreiden.com/)

Slidr is dual-licensed depending on the file type. This split keeps the design assets and presets freely shareable while ensuring the core system, CLI spawner, and slide generator executable code remain open over the network.

---

## Code — GNU Affero General Public License v3.0

The full text of the AGPL-3.0 license is in [LICENSE-CODE](LICENSE-CODE).

**What's covered:** all executable source code in this repository, including:

- Next.js application routes, layouts, and pages under `src/app/`
- React components under `src/components/`
- Shared utilities, LLM adapters, CLI spawners, and libraries under `src/lib/`
- Setup, diagnostics, and environment tools under `scripts/`
- Slash commands configurations under `.claude/`
- Any build, development, or deployment configs

**What this means in plain English:**

- You may use, modify, and distribute the code freely.
- If you modify the code and run it as a network service (e.g. host a custom fork of Slidr online), you must make your modified source available to the users of that service.
- Derivative works must be released under AGPL-3.0 or a compatible license.

If you need a different licensing arrangement for commercial use, contact [ceo@uitbreiden.com](mailto:ceo@uitbreiden.com).

---

## Content & Design Presets — Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0

The full text of the CC-BY-SA-4.0 license is in [LICENSE-CONTENT](LICENSE-CONTENT).

**What's covered:** all Markdown design files and preset configurations in this repository, including:

- Theme presets (`src/lib/themes/presets/*.md`)
- Custom design specifications (`DESIGN.md` format specs)
- Documentation and local metadata files (`AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, `README.md`)
